678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/youtube">YouTube</a>已透露计划推出标签，以表明视频是否使用人工智能 (AI) 制作。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/ai-music-oasis-liam-gallagher-drake-weeknd-3432529">在人工智能绿洲时代，平凡是没有意义的</a></strong></li></ul><p>YouTube 在今天的<a href="https://blog.youtube/inside-youtube/our-approach-to-responsible-ai-innovation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">博客更新</a>中宣布了这项新功能，并确认在“未来几个月”用户将被要求披露他们是否使用人工智能来创建内容。</p><p>如果用户确认他们使用人工智能来帮助制作视频，上传的标签将被添加到观众可见的内容中。</p><p> “为了解决这个问题，在接下来的几个月里，我们将推出更新，通知观众他们看到的内容是合成的，”更新中写道。</p><p>它补充说，该标签需要用在“现实”的材料上，并且在完整长度的视频和 YouTube Shorts 中都可以看到。话虽如此，“现实”一词仍然很广泛，有关受影响内容的更多细节预计将在稍后公布。</p><p> “具体来说，我们将要求创作者披露何时创建了真实的修改或合成内容，包括使用人工智能工具，”博客文章补充道。</p><p> “当创作者上传内容时，我们将提供新选项供他们选择，以表明内容包含真实的更改或合成材料。例如，这可能是人工智能生成的视频，真实地描述了从未发生过的事件，或者内容显示某人说或做了他们实际上没有做过的事情。” </p><figure id="attachment_3540167" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3540167" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3540167" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-studi@2000x1270.jpg" alt="家庭工作室库存照片" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-studi@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-studi@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-studi@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-studi@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-studi@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-studi@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3540167" class="wp-caption-text">家庭工作室库存照片。图片来源：Anastasiia Krivenok/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>后面提到的“敏感话题”被解释为包括有关选举、持续冲突、健康等的内容。</p><p>除了全面打击人工智能生成的内容外，YouTube 还确认了打击人工智能辅助音乐的计划，即模仿艺术家声音的内容。</p><p> “我们还为我们的音乐合作伙伴提供了请求删除人工智能生成的模仿艺术家独特的歌声或说唱声音的音乐内容的能力。在确定是否批准删除请求时，我们将考虑一些因素，例如内容是否是合成声音的新闻报道、分析或批评的主题。”</p><p>它继续说道：“这些删除请求将提供给代表参与 YouTube 早期人工智能音乐实验的艺术家的唱片公司或发行商。在接下来的几个月里，我们将继续扩大对更多品牌和分销商的访问范围。”</p><p>在博客文章中，没有透露这些变化生效的确切日期。 However, the platform has confirmed that users who fail to flag their AI-aided videos will be subject to video removal, and persistent offenders will be suspended from the YouTube Partner Programme. </p><figure id="attachment_3540169" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3540169" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3540169" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-Studio@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Musician in home music studio - stock photo" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-Studio@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-Studio@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-Studio@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-Studio@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-Studio@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Home-Studio@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3540169" class="wp-caption-text"> Musician in home music studio – stock photo. CREDIT: AleksandarNakic/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> YouTube&#39;s upcoming restrictions for AI-generated content follow that of the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-music-makers-share-five-fundamental-rules-for-industry-using-ai-3501881">Council of Music Makers (CMM), which in September published five fundamental rules</a> that it wants companies to embrace when it comes to developing music AI technologies.</p><p> These included respecting the personal data rights of music-makers, sharing the financial rewards of AI music fairly, and clearly labelling AI-generated works.</p><p> Artists from across the music industry have had mixed feelings about the increasing prominence of artificial intelligence in songwriting too.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/grimes">Grimes</a> , for instance, is supportive of the concept and even unveiled Elf.Tech – <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-is-beta-testing-her-own-ai-voice-mimicking-software-3438652">her own AI voice mimicking software that will allow fans to record and release music using her voice</a> .</p><p> Others are less accepting, however. Those who have criticised it include <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sting">Sting</a> , who said AI “doesn&#39;t impress” him, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stereophonics">Stereophonics</a> frontman <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/stereophonics-kelly-jones-hits-out-at-use-of-ai-in-songwriting-3473528">Kelly Jones, who said that art is about “a real person&#39;s expression”</a> , and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/guns-n-roses">Guns N&#39; Roses</a> bassist <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/duff-mckagan">Duff McKagan</a> who said <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/duff-mckagan-not-worried-about-ai-in-music-its-not-gonna-affect-my-creativity-3511911">he&#39;s “not worried” about AI in music as it won&#39;t “affect my creativity”</a> .</p><p> In other AI news, earlier this month a new study found that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/over-half-of-artists-would-conceal-ai-use-in-their-music-new-survey-finds-3527917">more than half of artists would choose not to disclose that they used AI to help make their music</a> .</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/youtube-to-label-videos-that-use-artificial-intelligence-a-i-3540160">YouTube to label videos that use AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
