Happier Than Ever&#39;</a> ] that&#39;s kind of about her.”</p><p> She added: “It&#39;s not only about her. I was just thinking about her when I was writing it. She was coming up, and she was younger than me, and nobody had ever been younger than me.”</p><p> &#39;Goldwing&#39; begins with some lines from a hymn that Eilish used to sing as a child in the Los Angeles Children&#39;s Chorus. Later, the star sings: “ <em>They&#39;re gonna tell you what you want to hear/ Then they&#39;re gonna disappear/ Gonna claim you like a souvenir/ Just to sell you in a year</em> .” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Billie Eilish - GOLDWING (Official Music Video)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YVZXDMUQQDo?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Eilish went on to recall in the conversation how she “felt so nervous” and “worried” about Rodrigo when the latter started “getting big” in the music industry.</p><p> “She came up in that acting world, and people are so weird. I don&#39;t know — I just felt very protective over her. And I feel that way to everyone,” she said.</p><p> “I just see myself in all these young girls. And it&#39;s the girls, man. Boys can handle themselves. They&#39;re dudes — they don&#39;t have to deal with it like we do. I just want to hold everybody in a little glass box and never let anything touch them.”</p><p> Back in September, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lana-del-rey-on-being-an-inspiration-to-billie-eilish-and-olivia-rodrigo-3501194">Lana Del Rey spoke about being an inspiration to Eilish and Rodrigo</a> – both of whom have attributed their inspiration within music to the singer-songwriter. “I love them and their music,” Del Rey explained.</p><p> Meanwhile, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/here-are-all-the-grammys-2024-nominations-3536101">Eilish and Rodrigo have recently been nominated for multiple Grammy Awards</a> . The two artists appear together in the Song Of The Year and Best Pop Solo Performance categories.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-speaks-out-against-being-sexualised-3538352">Eilish has also spoken out against the sexualisation she has faced throughout her career</a> – and how “nobody ever says a thing about men&#39;s bodies”.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-on-how-olivia-rodrigo-inspired-her-song-goldwing-3540090">Billie Eilish on how Olivia Rodrigo inspired her song &#39;Goldwing&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
